data.enText: on bed
a large piece of thin cloth used on a bed to lie on or lie under
Have you changed the sheets (= put clean sheets on the bed) ?

data.chText: 他钻进被子里，闭上了眼睛。
data.enText: He slid between the sheets and closed his eyes.
of paper

data.chText: 一张（通常指标准尺寸的纸）
data.enText: a piece of paper for writing or printing on, etc. usually in a standard size
a clean/blank sheet of paper (= with no writing on it)

data.chText: 请在接待处拿一份我们的免费资料。
data.enText: Pick up one of our free information sheets at reception.
flat thin piece

data.chText: 薄片，薄板（多指正方形或长方形的）
data.enText: a flat thin piece of any material, normally square or rectangular
a sheet of glass/steel
sheet metal (= metal that has been made into thin sheets)
Place the dough on a baking sheet (= for cooking sth in an oven) .
wide flat area
a wide flat area of sth, covering the surface of sth else
The road was covered with a sheet of ice.
of fire/water

data.chText: 一大片，一大堆，一大摊（移动的东西）
data.enText: a large moving mass of fire or water
a sheet of flame
The rain was coming down in sheets (= very heavily) .
on sail
a rope or chain fastened to the lower corner of a sail to hold it and to control the angle of the sail

data.text: There are other compounds ending sheet . You will find them at their place in the alphabet.
其他以sheet结尾的复合词，可在各字母中的适当位置查到。

data.enText: a clean sheet/slate

data.chText: 无过错记录；清白的历史
data.enText: a record of your work or behaviour that does not show any mistakes or bad things that you have done

data.chText: 没有任何政府执政一点也不失误。
data.enText: No government operates with a completely clean sheet.

data.chText: 他们在比赛中保持了未失一分的纪录。
data.enText: They kept a clean sheet in the match (= no goals were scored against them) .

tr: a large piece of fabric (usually canvas fabric) by means of which wind is used to propel a sailing vessel
bed linen consisting of a large rectangular piece of cotton or linen cloth
(nautical) a line (rope or chain) that regulates the angle at which a sail is set in relation to the wind
a flat artifact that is thin relative to its length and width
paper used for writing or printing
any broad thin expanse or surface

example: we will refer to the plane of the graph as the X-Y plane

value.def: A sheet is a large rectangular piece of cotton or other cloth that you sleep on or cover yourself with in a bed.

example.ex: Once a week, a maid changes the sheets.
example.tran: 女仆每星期换一次床单。

value.def: A sheet of paper is a rectangular piece of paper.

example.ex: I was able to fit it all on one sheet.
example.tran: 我能将全部内容都放在一页上。

value.def: You can use sheet to refer to a piece of paper which gives information about something.

example.ex: ...information sheets on each country in the world.
example.tran: 有关世界各国信息的简要记录

value.def: A sheet of glass, metal, or wood is a large, flat, thin piece of it.

example.ex: Overhead cranes were lifting giant sheets of steel...
example.tran: 高架起重机正吊起一块块巨大的钢板。

example.ex: Vinyl can be laid in sheet or tile form.
example.tran: 塑料地板分为卷材和块材两种。

value.tran: (玻璃、金属、木头等的)大块薄片，薄板

value.def: A sheet of something is a thin wide layer of it over the surface of something else.
value.tran: (覆盖在其他物体上的)一大片，一层

value.def: A sheet of fire or water is a fast-moving mass of it that is difficult to see through.

example.ex: The streets were now in one fierce sheet of flame...
example.tran: 街道上现在是一片火海。

example.ex: Sheets of rain slanted across the road.
example.tran: 倾盆大雨斜着打落在路上。

value.tran: 一团，一片，一股(迅速移动的火或水)

value.def: In sailing, a sheet is a line or rope used for controlling the position of a sail on a boat.
